        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 1 at 6:45PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 645 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Ayersville, or near Sandy Ridge, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Danville...
Eden...
Martinsville...
Wentworth...
Mayodan...
Madison...
and Stoneville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM EDT for
south central, central and west central Virginia.</instruction>
